  <front>
   <head>SONNET. INVITATION TO A FRIEND.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Since dark December shrouds the transient day,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And stormy Winds are howling in their ire,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Why com'st not , who always can'st inspire</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The soul of cheerfulness, and best array</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A sullen hour in smiles? — O! haste to pay</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The cordial visit sullen hours require!</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Around the circling Walls a glowing fire</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Shines; — but it vainly shines in this delay</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To blend thy spirit's warm Promethean light.</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Come then, at Science, and at Friendship's call,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Their vow'd Disciple; — come; for they invite;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The social Powers without thee languish all.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Come, — that I may not  the winds of night,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Nor  the heavy eve-drops as they fall!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
